{"video_id": "A5YG2qs98AU", "title": "SB 1.17.10-11 | Daily Evening Bhagavatam Discourse | HH Stoka Krishna Swami | 19-02-2023", "speaker": "HH Stoka Krishna Swami", "youtube_url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A5YG2qs98AU", "duration": 948, "segments": [{"start": 0.0, "end": 4.14, "text": " Om Agyanati Miran Dhasya Gyananjanishalakaya"}, {"start": 4.14, "end": 8.24, "text": " Chakshurun Militam Yena Tasmai Shri Gurave Namaha"}, {"start": 8.24, "end": 12.16, "text": " Namah Om Vishnupadaya Krishna Preshtaya Bhutale"}, {"start": 12.16, "end": 16.080000000000002, "text": " Shri Mate Bhakti Vedanta Swamin Nithinamine"}, {"start": 16.080000000000002, "end": 20.44, "text": " Namaste Saraswate Deve Gauravani Pracharine"}, {"start": 20.44, "end": 24.0, "text": " Nirvishesha Shunyavadi Pachatya Deshatarine"}, {"start": 24.64, "end": 28.0, "text": " Jaya Shri Krishna Chaitanya Prabhu Nithyananda"}, {"start": 28.0, "end": 33.26, "text": " Shri Advaita Gadadhara Shri Vasadi Gauravakta Vrinda"}, {"start": 33.26, "end": 37.18, "text": " Hare Krishna Hare Krishna Krishna Krishna Hare Hare"}, {"start": 37.18, "end": 40.82, "text": " Hare Rama Hare Rama Rama Rama Hare Hare"}, {"start": 40.82, "end": 45.0, "text": " Om Namo Bhagavate Vasudevaya Narayanam Namaskritya"}, {"start": 45.58, "end": 49.0, "text": " Naram Chai Vanarottamam Deveem Saraswateem Vyasam"}, {"start": 49.519999999999996, "end": 51.379999999999995, "text": " Tato Jayam Udi Rayet"}, {"start": 51.379999999999995, "end": 56.260000000000005, "text": " In this session we will be discussing from two verses,"}, {"start": 56.260000000000005, "end": 57.980000000000004, "text": " the 10th and the 11th verses."}, {"start": 58.0, "end": 61.84, "text": " of the 17th chapter of the first canto of Srimad Bhagavatam."}, {"start": 63.44, "end": 66.18, "text": " Both these verses are given together by Srila Prabhupada,"}, {"start": 66.26, "end": 67.7, "text": " so I shall read both of them,"}, {"start": 68.26, "end": 70.04, "text": " the 10th verse and the 11th verse."}, {"start": 70.04, "end": 73.24, "text": " Yasya Rashtre Prajasarvaha"}, {"start": 73.24, "end": 79.06, "text": " Trasyante Sadhya Asadubihi"}, {"start": 79.06, "end": 83.08, "text": " Tasya Mattasya Nashyanti"}, {"start": 83.08, "end": 87.76, "text": " Keertir Ayur Bhagogatihi"}, {"start": 88.0, "end": 93.86, "text": " Esha Ragnam Parodharmo"}, {"start": 93.86, "end": 97.68, "text": " Hyartanam Aarti Nigraha"}, {"start": 97.68, "end": 100.44, "text": " Ataenam Vadishyami"}, {"start": 100.44, "end": 103.6, "text": " Bhutadruham Asaptamam"}, {"start": 103.6, "end": 109.66, "text": " The meaning of these two verses is as follows."}, {"start": 110.44, "end": 113.26, "text": " O chaste one, the king's good name,"}, {"start": 113.26, "end": 117.76, "text": " duration of life and good rebirth vanish."}, {"start": 118.0, "end": 120.76, "text": " When all kinds of living beings are terrified"}, {"start": 120.76, "end": 122.36, "text": " by miscreants in his kingdom,"}, {"start": 123.1, "end": 126.04, "text": " it is certainly the prime duty of the king"}, {"start": 126.04, "end": 129.5, "text": " to subdue first the sufferings of those who suffer."}, {"start": 130.56, "end": 134.38, "text": " Therefore, I must kill this most wretched man"}, {"start": 134.38, "end": 138.04, "text": " because he is violent against other living beings."}, {"start": 140.96, "end": 143.2, "text": " So Srila Prabhupada writes elaborate purport"}, {"start": 143.2, "end": 145.44, "text": " for these two verses."}, {"start": 145.92000000000002, "end": 146.96, "text": " Purport is as follows."}, {"start": 146.96, "end": 147.98, "text": " When all kinds of living beings are terrified by miscreants in his kingdom,"}, {"start": 147.98, "end": 151.54, "text": " when there is some disturbance caused by wild animals in a village or town,"}, {"start": 151.54, "end": 154.5, "text": " the police or others take action to kill them."}, {"start": 155.35999999999999, "end": 159.22, "text": " Similarly, it is the duty of the government to kill at once"}, {"start": 159.22, "end": 164.42, "text": " all bad social elements such as thieves, decoits and murderers."}, {"start": 165.28, "end": 169.06, "text": " The same punishment is also due to animal killers"}, {"start": 169.06, "end": 172.7, "text": " because the animals of the state are also called praja."}, {"start": 173.83999999999997, "end": 177.7, "text": " The word praja that is used, citizen."}, {"start": 177.98, "end": 180.48, "text": " In English we say citizen, praja."}, {"start": 181.54, "end": 184.89999999999998, "text": " Praja means one who has taken birth in the state."}, {"start": 186.35999999999999, "end": 187.54, "text": " Ja means to take birth."}, {"start": 189.7, "end": 194.57999999999998, "text": " So this praja includes both men and animals,"}, {"start": 194.83999999999997, "end": 197.66, "text": " especially the cows and bulls."}, {"start": 198.95999999999998, "end": 200.6, "text": " They are reared by human beings,"}, {"start": 200.95999999999998, "end": 204.72, "text": " especially for Brahmanical culture."}, {"start": 205.98, "end": 207.83999999999997, "text": " Any living being who takes birth in the state,"}, {"start": 207.84, "end": 211.76, "text": " has the primary right to live under the protection of the king."}, {"start": 215.12, "end": 217.66, "text": " Any living being who takes birth in the state,"}, {"start": 218.46, "end": 220.56, "text": " be it an animal or a human being."}, {"start": 221.54, "end": 225.52, "text": " The jungle animals are also subject to the king"}, {"start": 225.52, "end": 227.7, "text": " and they also have a right to live."}, {"start": 228.76, "end": 231.44, "text": " What to speak of, as Prabhupada says,"}, {"start": 231.52, "end": 234.34, "text": " what to speak of the domestic animals like the cows and bulls,"}, {"start": 234.34, "end": 235.8, "text": " even the jungle animals,"}, {"start": 236.22, "end": 237.34, "text": " they cannot be indiscriminately,"}, {"start": 237.84, "end": 243.84, "text": " they cannot be indiscriminately killed by anyone."}, {"start": 243.84, "end": 250.04, "text": " So, especially the cows and bulls must be protected by the king."}, {"start": 252.04, "end": 254.14000000000001, "text": " Also, as Prabhupada further explains,"}, {"start": 254.68, "end": 257.44, "text": " any living being, if he terrifies other living beings,"}, {"start": 257.52, "end": 258.92, "text": " is a most wretched subject"}, {"start": 258.92, "end": 262.22, "text": " and the king should at once kill such a disturbing element."}, {"start": 262.96, "end": 266.0, "text": " To maintain peace, to maintain law and order,"}, {"start": 266.0, "end": 267.42, "text": " the king should,"}, {"start": 267.84000000000003, "end": 273.84000000000003, "text": " impose very strict punishment"}, {"start": 273.84000000000003, "end": 278.20000000000005, "text": " in order to protect the innocent."}, {"start": 280.20000000000005, "end": 283.24, "text": " As the wild animal is killed when it creates disturbances,"}, {"start": 283.46000000000004, "end": 287.6, "text": " similarly, any man who unnecessarily kills or terrifies the jungle animals"}, {"start": 287.6, "end": 290.66, "text": " or other animals must be punished at once."}, {"start": 292.28000000000003, "end": 294.00000000000006, "text": " By the law of the Supreme Lord,"}, {"start": 294.00000000000006, "end": 296.34000000000003, "text": " all living beings in whatever shape they may be"}, {"start": 296.34000000000003, "end": 297.56000000000006, "text": " are the sons of the Lord,"}, {"start": 297.84000000000003, "end": 300.40000000000003, "text": " and no one has any right to kill another animal"}, {"start": 300.40000000000003, "end": 303.84000000000003, "text": " unless it is so ordered by the codes of natural law."}, {"start": 305.84000000000003, "end": 309.84000000000003, "text": " What is wrong in killing an animal by a human being?"}, {"start": 309.84000000000003, "end": 311.84000000000003, "text": " Prabhupada points out that"}, {"start": 311.84000000000003, "end": 315.84000000000003, "text": " the tiger can kill a lower animal for his subsistence"}, {"start": 315.84000000000003, "end": 318.84000000000003, "text": " because that is the food for the tiger"}, {"start": 318.84000000000003, "end": 322.84000000000003, "text": " ordained by the higher laws."}, {"start": 322.84000000000003, "end": 326.84000000000003, "text": " But a man cannot kill an animal for his subsistence."}, {"start": 326.84000000000003, "end": 328.84000000000003, "text": " That is the law of God"}, {"start": 328.84000000000003, "end": 334.84000000000003, "text": " who has created the law that a living being subsists by eating another living being."}, {"start": 334.84000000000003, "end": 338.84000000000003, "text": " Jeevo Jeevasya Jeevanam"}, {"start": 338.84000000000003, "end": 340.84000000000003, "text": " This is explained in the earlier chapter,"}, {"start": 340.84000000000003, "end": 344.84000000000003, "text": " 13th chapter of the first canto of Bhagavatam,"}, {"start": 344.84000000000003, "end": 351.84000000000003, "text": " that we cannot eat some matter,"}, {"start": 351.84000000000003, "end": 353.84000000000003, "text": " dead matter, we cannot eat."}, {"start": 353.84000000000003, "end": 355.84000000000003, "text": " We have to eat something"}, {"start": 355.84000000000003, "end": 357.84000000000003, "text": " for our subsistence,"}, {"start": 357.84000000000003, "end": 361.84000000000003, "text": " something which is like a living being."}, {"start": 361.84000000000003, "end": 366.84000000000003, "text": " Thus the vegetarians are also living by eating other living beings."}, {"start": 366.84000000000003, "end": 368.84000000000003, "text": " Therefore the law is that"}, {"start": 368.84000000000003, "end": 372.84000000000003, "text": " one should live only by eating specific living beings"}, {"start": 372.84000000000003, "end": 375.84000000000003, "text": " as ordained by the law of God."}, {"start": 377.84000000000003, "end": 380.84000000000003, "text": " And that is explained in the Isopanishad as follows."}, {"start": 380.84000000000003, "end": 382.84000000000003, "text": " The Isopanishad directs that"}, {"start": 382.84000000000003, "end": 384.84000000000003, "text": " one should live by direction of the Lord"}, {"start": 384.84000000000003, "end": 387.84000000000003, "text": " and not at one's sweet will."}, {"start": 387.84000000000003, "end": 390.84000000000003, "text": " People say,"}, {"start": 390.84000000000003, "end": 394.84000000000003, "text": " my preference to eat meat."}, {"start": 394.84000000000003, "end": 396.84000000000003, "text": " You may prefer to eat vegetables,"}, {"start": 396.84000000000003, "end": 398.84000000000003, "text": " but my preference to eat meat."}, {"start": 398.84000000000003, "end": 403.84000000000003, "text": " This is the argument that is given by some people who are non-vegetarians."}, {"start": 403.84000000000003, "end": 405.84000000000003, "text": " But Prabhupada says,"}, {"start": 405.84000000000003, "end": 410.84000000000003, "text": " a man can subsist on varieties of grains, fruits and milk ordained by God."}, {"start": 410.84000000000003, "end": 413.84000000000003, "text": " There is no need of animal food."}, {"start": 414.84000000000003, "end": 416.84000000000003, "text": " For a human being,"}, {"start": 416.84000000000003, "end": 419.84000000000003, "text": " save and accept in particular cases."}, {"start": 421.84000000000003, "end": 426.84000000000003, "text": " Let's say there is no availability of"}, {"start": 426.84000000000003, "end": 430.84000000000003, "text": " food grains or fruits or vegetables or milk."}, {"start": 430.84000000000003, "end": 435.84000000000003, "text": " Then under those extreme circumstances"}, {"start": 435.84000000000003, "end": 438.84000000000003, "text": " one may eat some animal flesh."}, {"start": 439.84000000000003, "end": 443.84000000000003, "text": " Otherwise there is no reason to eat animal flesh."}, {"start": 444.84000000000003, "end": 447.84000000000003, "text": " The illusion king or executive head,"}, {"start": 447.84000000000003, "end": 451.84000000000003, "text": " even though sometimes advertised as a great philosopher and learned scholar,"}, {"start": 451.84000000000003, "end": 453.84000000000003, "text": " will allow slaughterhouses in the state"}, {"start": 453.84000000000003, "end": 456.84000000000003, "text": " without knowing that torturing poor animals"}, {"start": 456.84000000000003, "end": 458.84000000000003, "text": " clears the way to hell"}, {"start": 458.84000000000003, "end": 461.84000000000003, "text": " to such foolish kings or executive heads."}, {"start": 461.84000000000003, "end": 465.84000000000003, "text": " See, above the laws enforced by a government or a king,"}, {"start": 466.84000000000003, "end": 470.84000000000003, "text": " there are laws of God operating"}, {"start": 470.84000000000003, "end": 473.84000000000003, "text": " in this material world."}, {"start": 474.84000000000003, "end": 476.84000000000003, "text": " So,"}, {"start": 476.84000000000003, "end": 481.84000000000003, "text": " their future is very very very very dark."}, {"start": 481.84000000000003, "end": 483.84000000000003, "text": " Those who are animal killers."}, {"start": 486.84000000000003, "end": 490.84000000000003, "text": " The executive head must always be alert to the safety of the prajas,"}, {"start": 490.84000000000003, "end": 491.84000000000003, "text": " both man and animal,"}, {"start": 491.84000000000003, "end": 496.84000000000003, "text": " and inquire whether a particular living being is harassed at any place by another living being."}, {"start": 496.84000000000003, "end": 501.84000000000003, "text": " The harassing living being must be at once caught and put to death"}, {"start": 501.84000000000003, "end": 503.84000000000003, "text": " as shown by Maharaj Parichar."}, {"start": 504.84000000000003, "end": 507.84000000000003, "text": " The king's duty is to give protection"}, {"start": 507.84000000000003, "end": 510.84000000000003, "text": " and punish the culprits"}, {"start": 510.84000000000003, "end": 513.84, "text": " without showing any"}, {"start": 513.84, "end": 518.84, "text": " sentimental compassion or mercy."}, {"start": 518.84, "end": 519.84, "text": " No."}, {"start": 521.84, "end": 522.84, "text": " So Srila Prabhupada says,"}, {"start": 522.84, "end": 524.84, "text": " the people's government or government by the people"}, {"start": 524.84, "end": 528.84, "text": " should not allow killing of innocent animals"}, {"start": 528.84, "end": 531.84, "text": " by the sweet will of foolish government men."}, {"start": 531.84, "end": 534.84, "text": " These government people don't care"}, {"start": 534.84, "end": 538.84, "text": " if animals are killed indiscriminately."}, {"start": 538.84, "end": 540.84, "text": " And actually,"}, {"start": 540.84, "end": 543.84, "text": " the government should not allow that."}, {"start": 543.84, "end": 546.84, "text": " If they want proper law and order,"}, {"start": 546.84, "end": 548.84, "text": " if they want peace in the society,"}, {"start": 548.84, "end": 550.84, "text": " they must know the codes of God"}, {"start": 550.84, "end": 552.84, "text": " as mentioned in the revealed scriptures,"}, {"start": 552.84, "end": 554.84, "text": " Dharma Shastra."}, {"start": 554.84, "end": 556.84, "text": " Manusmriti, Parashara Smriti,"}, {"start": 556.84, "end": 558.84, "text": " Agnya Varkya Smriti."}, {"start": 558.84, "end": 559.84, "text": " They should know that."}, {"start": 559.84, "end": 560.84, "text": " Perfect."}, {"start": 560.84, "end": 564.84, "text": " Correct directions are given"}, {"start": 564.84, "end": 566.84, "text": " in the revealed scriptures"}, {"start": 566.84, "end": 567.84, "text": " for governance,"}, {"start": 567.84, "end": 571.84, "text": " how to rule the kingdom or the state."}, {"start": 571.84, "end": 573.84, "text": " Maharaj Parikshit quotes here"}, {"start": 573.84, "end": 575.84, "text": " that according to the codes of God,"}, {"start": 575.84, "end": 577.84, "text": " the irresponsible king or state executive"}, {"start": 577.84, "end": 579.84, "text": " jeopardizes his good name,"}, {"start": 579.84, "end": 581.84, "text": " duration of life,"}, {"start": 581.84, "end": 582.84, "text": " power and strength"}, {"start": 582.84, "end": 584.84, "text": " and ultimately his progressive march"}, {"start": 584.84, "end": 588.84, "text": " towards a better life and salvation after death."}, {"start": 588.84, "end": 589.84, "text": " See, this is very important."}, {"start": 589.84, "end": 591.84, "text": " This understanding that"}, {"start": 591.84, "end": 594.84, "text": " every living being is spirit-soul,"}, {"start": 594.84, "end": 596.84, "text": " not the body."}, {"start": 596.84, "end": 599.84, "text": " And"}, {"start": 599.84, "end": 602.84, "text": " the soul actually"}, {"start": 602.84, "end": 606.84, "text": " is meant for making progress."}, {"start": 606.84, "end": 608.84, "text": " The actual living being"}, {"start": 608.84, "end": 610.84, "text": " inside the body,"}, {"start": 610.84, "end": 613.84, "text": " the living entity as we say,"}, {"start": 613.84, "end": 616.84, "text": " the particular person inside the body"}, {"start": 616.84, "end": 619.84, "text": " is meant for progressing towards"}, {"start": 619.84, "end": 623.84, "text": " a better life."}, {"start": 623.84, "end": 626.84, "text": " And that is the opportunity"}, {"start": 626.84, "end": 630.84, "text": " in this material world."}, {"start": 630.84, "end": 632.84, "text": " Such foolish men do not even believe"}, {"start": 632.84, "end": 634.84, "text": " in the existence of the next life."}, {"start": 634.84, "end": 636.84, "text": " They don't even know"}, {"start": 636.84, "end": 637.84, "text": " there is a next life."}, {"start": 637.84, "end": 639.84, "text": " They are so ignorant."}, {"start": 639.84, "end": 640.84, "text": " Or if they are informed,"}, {"start": 640.84, "end": 641.84, "text": " they think,"}, {"start": 641.84, "end": 644.84, "text": " oh, we don't believe in that."}, {"start": 644.84, "end": 647.84, "text": " Now this belief system"}, {"start": 647.84, "end": 654.84, "text": " under the situation where"}, {"start": 654.84, "end": 657.84, "text": " they are ignorant people,"}, {"start": 657.84, "end": 659.84, "text": " certain laws that are working,"}, {"start": 659.84, "end": 660.84, "text": " they do not know."}, {"start": 660.84, "end": 662.84, "text": " Just like foolish people,"}, {"start": 662.84, "end": 666.84, "text": " they do not know their suffering"}, {"start": 666.84, "end": 669.84, "text": " is caused by their own"}, {"start": 669.84, "end": 674.84, "text": " previous sinful activities."}, {"start": 674.84, "end": 676.84, "text": " That they do not know."}, {"start": 676.84, "end": 678.84, "text": " Many foolish people are there,"}, {"start": 678.84, "end": 680.84, "text": " ignorant people are there."}, {"start": 680.84, "end": 683.84, "text": " And all kinds of non-believers,"}, {"start": 683.84, "end": 684.84, "text": " as we say,"}, {"start": 684.84, "end": 686.84, "text": " atheists,"}, {"start": 686.84, "end": 687.84, "text": " agnostics,"}, {"start": 687.84, "end": 691.84, "text": " upstarts,"}, {"start": 691.84, "end": 693.84, "text": " ignorant people,"}, {"start": 693.84, "end": 694.84, "text": " they suffer,"}, {"start": 694.84, "end": 695.84, "text": " but they do not know"}, {"start": 695.84, "end": 698.84, "text": " why they are suffering."}, {"start": 698.84, "end": 700.84, "text": " Especially when they are"}, {"start": 700.84, "end": 702.84, "text": " afflicted by some"}, {"start": 702.84, "end": 705.84, "text": " disease."}, {"start": 705.84, "end": 708.84, "text": " Or they are afflicted by some"}, {"start": 708.84, "end": 711.84, "text": " pain."}, {"start": 711.84, "end": 714.84, "text": " Some natural calamity."}, {"start": 714.84, "end": 717.84, "text": " They do not know"}, {"start": 717.84, "end": 719.84, "text": " why they were"}, {"start": 719.84, "end": 722.84, "text": " subject to some"}, {"start": 722.84, "end": 724.84, "text": " some disaster,"}, {"start": 724.84, "end": 727.84, "text": " natural disaster."}, {"start": 727.84, "end": 729.84, "text": " They do not know."}, {"start": 729.84, "end": 730.84, "text": " But,"}, {"start": 730.84, "end": 732.84, "text": " it is not that"}, {"start": 732.84, "end": 734.84, "text": " sometimes there is some"}, {"start": 734.84, "end": 735.84, "text": " natural calamity"}, {"start": 735.84, "end": 738.84, "text": " and we have to"}, {"start": 738.84, "end": 739.84, "text": " simply face it."}, {"start": 739.84, "end": 740.84, "text": " No."}, {"start": 740.84, "end": 742.84, "text": " It is not like that."}, {"start": 742.84, "end": 744.84, "text": " It is completely controlled."}, {"start": 744.84, "end": 746.84, "text": " Nature is controlled by God."}, {"start": 746.84, "end": 748.84, "text": " And nature,"}, {"start": 748.84, "end": 750.84, "text": " under God's direction,"}, {"start": 750.84, "end": 752.84, "text": " gives punishment to people"}, {"start": 752.84, "end": 755.84, "text": " who are sinful."}, {"start": 755.84, "end": 757.84, "text": " And they suffer in proportion"}, {"start": 757.84, "end": 759.84, "text": " to their"}, {"start": 759.84, "end": 762.84, "text": " past sinful activities."}, {"start": 762.84, "end": 764.84, "text": " Violation of the codes of God."}, {"start": 764.84, "end": 768.84, "text": " So,"}, {"start": 768.84, "end": 770.84, "text": " Srila Prabhupada says,"}, {"start": 770.84, "end": 772.84, "text": " politicians,"}, {"start": 772.84, "end": 774.84, "text": " they are ignorant"}, {"start": 774.84, "end": 776.84, "text": " and one such politician"}, {"start": 776.84, "end": 777.84, "text": " has written,"}, {"start": 777.84, "end": 779.84, "text": " I do not believe in any"}, {"start": 779.84, "end": 780.84, "text": " such ceremonies"}, {"start": 780.84, "end": 781.84, "text": " and to submit to them"}, {"start": 781.84, "end": 782.84, "text": " even as a matter of form"}, {"start": 782.84, "end": 783.84, "text": " would be hypocrisy"}, {"start": 783.84, "end": 784.84, "text": " in an attempt to"}, {"start": 784.84, "end": 785.84, "text": " delude ourselves"}, {"start": 785.84, "end": 786.84, "text": " and others."}, {"start": 786.84, "end": 788.84, "text": " I have no religious sentiment"}, {"start": 788.84, "end": 790.84, "text": " in the matter."}, {"start": 790.84, "end": 791.84, "text": " Some politician"}, {"start": 791.84, "end": 792.84, "text": " has said,"}, {"start": 792.84, "end": 794.84, "text": " that he doesn't believe in"}, {"start": 794.84, "end": 796.84, "text": " life after death."}, {"start": 796.84, "end": 798.84, "text": " He doesn't believe in the codes of"}, {"start": 798.84, "end": 799.84, "text": " God"}, {"start": 799.84, "end": 802.84, "text": " as given in the authentic scriptures."}, {"start": 802.84, "end": 804.84, "text": " Such people"}, {"start": 804.84, "end": 806.84, "text": " are"}, {"start": 806.84, "end": 809.84, "text": " totally ignorant"}, {"start": 809.84, "end": 811.84, "text": " unlike Maharaj Pariksit."}, {"start": 812.84, "end": 813.84, "text": " So,"}, {"start": 813.84, "end": 815.84, "text": " Maharaj Pariksit was pious"}, {"start": 815.84, "end": 817.84, "text": " according to scriptural codes."}, {"start": 818.84, "end": 820.84, "text": " He was having a solid basis"}, {"start": 820.84, "end": 822.84, "text": " for governance."}, {"start": 822.84, "end": 823.84, "text": " Whereas,"}, {"start": 823.84, "end": 824.84, "text": " the modern politician"}, {"start": 824.84, "end": 825.84, "text": " goes by his personal"}, {"start": 825.84, "end": 827.84, "text": " belief and sentiments."}, {"start": 830.84, "end": 831.84, "text": " He just"}, {"start": 831.84, "end": 832.84, "text": " conducts himself"}, {"start": 832.84, "end": 833.84, "text": " and he"}, {"start": 833.84, "end": 835.84, "text": " enforces law"}, {"start": 835.84, "end": 836.84, "text": " based on his personal"}, {"start": 836.84, "end": 838.84, "text": " sentiments."}, {"start": 838.84, "end": 839.84, "text": " Which is"}, {"start": 839.84, "end": 841.84, "text": " very very dangerous."}, {"start": 841.84, "end": 842.84, "text": " Because,"}, {"start": 842.84, "end": 844.84, "text": " I may differ"}, {"start": 844.84, "end": 845.84, "text": " from another person."}, {"start": 845.84, "end": 846.84, "text": " Some other person"}, {"start": 846.84, "end": 848.84, "text": " may differ from somebody else."}, {"start": 848.84, "end": 850.84, "text": " Is that the way to"}, {"start": 850.84, "end": 852.84, "text": " actually"}, {"start": 852.84, "end": 854.84, "text": " conduct the government?"}, {"start": 854.84, "end": 856.84, "text": " It is totally"}, {"start": 856.84, "end": 859.84, "text": " irrational."}, {"start": 859.84, "end": 861.84, "text": " It's meaningless."}, {"start": 861.84, "end": 862.84, "text": " So,"}, {"start": 862.84, "end": 863.84, "text": " Prabhupada says,"}, {"start": 863.84, "end": 865.84, "text": " after all,"}, {"start": 866.84, "end": 869.84, "text": " even the so-called great man"}, {"start": 869.84, "end": 870.84, "text": " in this material world"}, {"start": 870.84, "end": 872.84, "text": " is a conditioned soul."}, {"start": 872.84, "end": 875.84, "text": " He is bound by his hands and feet."}, {"start": 875.84, "end": 877.84, "text": " By the ropes of material nature."}, {"start": 877.84, "end": 879.84, "text": " And still he thinks that"}, {"start": 879.84, "end": 881.84, "text": " he can act whimsically."}, {"start": 882.84, "end": 884.84, "text": " So the conclusion is,"}, {"start": 884.84, "end": 886.84, "text": " during Pariksit Maharaj's time,"}, {"start": 886.84, "end": 888.84, "text": " people were happy."}, {"start": 888.84, "end": 890.84, "text": " Animals were given proper protection."}, {"start": 890.84, "end": 892.84, "text": " And,"}, {"start": 892.84, "end": 893.84, "text": " there was"}, {"start": 893.84, "end": 895.84, "text": " peace and prosperity"}, {"start": 895.84, "end": 897.84, "text": " in the kingdom."}, {"start": 897.84, "end": 898.84, "text": " And it was"}, {"start": 898.84, "end": 900.84, "text": " experienced by everyone."}, {"start": 900.84, "end": 902.84, "text": " And modern day"}, {"start": 902.84, "end": 904.84, "text": " situation is so bad."}, {"start": 904.84, "end": 907.84, "text": " People are suffering in so many ways."}, {"start": 907.84, "end": 909.84, "text": " So many ways."}, {"start": 909.84, "end": 912.84, "text": " Except those who are"}, {"start": 912.84, "end": 913.84, "text": " truly God conscious."}, {"start": 913.84, "end": 915.84, "text": " All others have to suffer in"}, {"start": 915.84, "end": 917.84, "text": " so many ways."}, {"start": 917.84, "end": 919.84, "text": " So,"}, {"start": 919.84, "end": 921.84, "text": " the"}, {"start": 921.84, "end": 923.84, "text": " conclusion is that"}, {"start": 923.84, "end": 925.84, "text": " we should be God conscious."}, {"start": 925.84, "end": 927.84, "text": " And we should follow"}, {"start": 927.84, "end": 929.84, "text": " the God given"}, {"start": 931.84, "end": 933.84, "text": " directions."}, {"start": 933.84, "end": 934.84, "text": " And then,"}, {"start": 934.84, "end": 936.84, "text": " individually and collectively,"}, {"start": 936.84, "end": 937.84, "text": " we can be happy,"}, {"start": 937.84, "end": 938.84, "text": " peaceful,"}, {"start": 939.84, "end": 941.84, "text": " we can live a peaceful life,"}, {"start": 941.84, "end": 944.84, "text": " and we can expect prosperity."}, {"start": 944.84, "end": 945.84, "text": " I'll stop here."}, {"start": 945.84, "end": 946.84, "text": " Thank you very much."}, {"start": 946.84, "end": 947.84, "text": " Hare Krishna."}]}